data.chText: 难以忘怀的；令人难忘的
data.enText: if sth is unforgettable , you cannot forget it, usually because it is so beautiful, interesting, enjoyable, etc.

ex.chText: 这是让他难忘的一次经历。
ex.enText: It was a memorable experience for him.

ex.chText: 她丈夫想让蜜月之旅成为她永远难忘的旅行。
ex.enText: Her husband wants to make their honeymoon a memorable trip for her.

synonyms.bx: 指经历等很愉快或不同寻常而值得记住的，含主动去记住之意。

ex.chText: 她的舞蹈是一次令人难忘的表演。
ex.enText: Her dancing made an impressive performance.

ex.chText: 这是他近年来给人印象最深的作品之一。
ex.enText: This is one of his most impressive works of recent years.

ex.chText: 12号选手在辩论中表现十分出色。
ex.enText: Contestant No. 12 was very impressive in the debate.

synonyms.bx: 指事物或人因某种优点、特性等令人赞叹的。

ex.chText: 到罗马一游将会令人永远难忘。
ex.enText: A visit to Rome will be unforgettable.

synonyms.bx: 尤指经历、景象等特别美好而无法忘记的，含想忘也忘不了之意。

value.def: If you describe something as unforgettable, you mean that it is, for example, extremely beautiful, enjoyable, or unusual, so that you remember it for a long time. You can also refer to extremely unpleasant things as unforgettable .

example.ex: A visit to the Museum is an unforgettable experience...
example.tran: 参观博物馆是一段令人难忘的经历。

example.ex: A bright shooting star, or meteor, is an unforgettable sight.
example.tran: 明亮的流星，或者说陨石，是番难忘的景象。

example.ex: ...those unforgettable songs we love to hate.
example.tran: 那些我们又爱又恨的难忘歌曲

example.ex: ...the leisure activities that will make your holiday unforgettable.
example.tran: 让假日成为难忘记忆的休闲活动
一位令人难忘的独特的表演者

trans: 不了情；刻骨铭心的爱；未了情；藕断丝连；意难忘
